					<h4>Local Music Sound Off</h4>
		
		<h1>Bright Channel&#8217;s &#8220;Disillusionist&#8221;</h1>
		<h2><i></i></h2>
		<div class="text-feature_print">
							<p>By Jenny Shank, 2-24-06</p>
			
							<table width="25" align="right" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
					<tr>
						<td>&nbsp;</td>
						<td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/thumbnails_feature/bcpracticetrees3_400p_thumb.jpg" class="thumbnail-feature" border="0" align="right" width="150" height="112" /></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/spacer.gif" width="1" height="3" border="0" /></td></tr>

					
					<tr><td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/spacer.gif" width="1" height="3" border="0" /></td></tr>
				</table>
			
							Denver indie rockers Bright Channel will celebrate the release of their sophomore album, <i>Self-Propelled</i> at the <a href="http://www.hi-dive.com" title="Hi-Dive">Hi-Dive</a> on Friday, February 24.  Tickets are $8, and Monofog and Moccasin will open.  For music fans who prefer not to venture out of their homes, Bright Channel will also be featured on the <i>Local Shakedown</i> broadcast on Radio 1190.  The show airs 4-6 p.m. tonight on 1190 AM or <a href="http://www.radio1190.org/" title="www.radio1190.org">www.radio1190.org</a>.<br />
<br />
The new album marks a change for the groupâ€”its first album was produced by Steve Albini, famous for his production work with Nirvana, PJ Harvey, and The Pixies.  This time Bright Channel recorded the album by themselves in their own <a href="http://www.flightapproved.com/cart.html" title="Flight Approved Studios">Flight Approved Studios</a>.  The result is a murkier affair, with all the clash and clamor left in.<br />
<br />
Bright Channel has offered <i>New West</i> readers a track from <i>Self Propelled</i>.  <a href="http://www.newwest.net/MP3s/brightchanneldisillusionist.mp3" title="Click here to listen to "Disillusionist."">Click here to listen to "Disillusionist."</a><br />
<br />
Next month, Bright Channel plans to tour through Albuquerque, New Mexico and Austin Texas in time for the South By Southwest Festival.  The band then returns to Denver, where it'll open for Pink Mountaintops and Two Gallants at the Hi-Dive on March 24.<br />

						<b>[End of article]</b>
